race.comment: EARTHSTORM (3) has been an eye catcher in both runs this time in, finishing 3.3L away in the Jungle Dawn last start. She'll find this much easier today and the step up in trip looks a good move. Likely to get back in the run but can finish with a flurry down the outside. REGAL STATUE (9) looks poised to strike third-up into the campaign, finishing 3.7L away over 1200m last start after settling well out the back. We'll get a good line on that form through the Black Heart Bart and she draws better this time around. Can sit handier and land the knockout blow. MAGNA'S CHOICE (11) gets the blinkers on first time today back in trip and the booking of Pike is a positive lead. Form out of his past couple has been strong and he's expected to make his presence felt. DUG ANOTHER HOLE (5) was strong fresh and can be in the finish again. CLIMB ON TOP (4) is better than he's shown his past couple and can bounce back.
